[SN]TITLE[SN]
Londonderry: Boy dies after being hit by car on Lone Moor Road

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A two-year-old boy has died after being hit by a car in Londonderry.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The collision happened on the Lone Moor Road at about 13:15 BST on Sunday. The car involved was a silver Citroen Picasso.
The road remains closed while police continue with their inquiries. Insp David McIlwaine has appealed for witnesses to contact police.
